STEP|33|Step 1: Choose quantization method**
STEP|34|**AWQ**: Best for 70B models, minimal accuracy loss
STEP|35|**GPTQ**: Wide model support, good compression
STEP|36|**FP8**: Fastest on H100 GPUs
STEP|37|Step 2: Find or create quantized model**
STEP|38|Step 3: Launch with quantization flag**
STEP|39|Step 4: Verify accuracy**
STEP|40|Use vLLM when:**
STEP|41|Deploying production LLM APIs (100+ req/sec)
STEP|42|Serving OpenAI-compatible endpoints
STEP|43|Limited GPU memory but need large models
STEP|44|Multi-user applications (chatbots, assistants)
STEP|45|Need low latency with high throughput
STEP|46|Use alternatives instead:**
STEP|47|**llama.cpp**: CPU/edge inference, single-user
STEP|48|**HuggingFace transformers**: Research, prototyping, one-off generation
STEP|49|**TensorRT-LLM**: NVIDIA-only, need absolute maximum performance
STEP|50|**Text-Generation-Inference**: Already in HuggingFace ecosystem
STEP|51|Issue: Out of memory during model loading**
STEP|52|Issue: Slow first token (TTFT > 1 second)**
STEP|53|Issue: Model not found error**
STEP|54|Issue: Low throughput (<50 req/sec)**
STEP|55|Issue: Inference slower than expected**
STEP|56|Server deployment patterns**: See [references/server-deployment.md](references/server-deployment.md) for Docker, Kubernetes, and load balancing configurations.
STEP|57|Performance optimization**: See [references/optimization.md](references/optimization.md) for PagedAttention tuning, continuous batching details, and benchmark results.
STEP|58|Quantization guide**: See [references/quantization.md](references/quantization.md) for AWQ/GPTQ/FP8 setup, model preparation, and accuracy comparisons.
STEP|59|Troubleshooting**: See [references/troubleshooting.md](references/troubleshooting.md) for detailed error messages, debugging steps, and performance diagnostics.
STEP|60|**Small models (7B-13B)**: 1x A10 (24GB) or A100 (40GB)
STEP|61|**Medium models (30B-40B)**: 2x A100 (40GB) with tensor parallelism
STEP|62|**Large models (70B+)**: 4x A100 (40GB) or 2x A100 (80GB), use AWQ/GPTQ
STEP|63|Official docs: https://docs.vllm.ai
STEP|64|GitHub: https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm
STEP|65|Paper: "Efficient Memory Management for Large Language Model Serving with PagedAttention" (SOSP 2023)
STEP|66|Community: https://discuss.vllm.ai
